OL,3,C'No one should have to have
OL,4,Ccongratulations and condolences on the
OL,5,Csame day'
OL,7,F"Learning this was devastating. It is
OL,8,Fmy view that there is a culture of
OL,9,Ffailing to recognise when specialist
OL,10,Fguidance is needed at Wythenshawe
OL,11,FHospital."
OL,13,FThe hospital has admitted its care
OL,14,Ffell short of expected standards, and
OL,15,Fthat it has committed to making
OL,16,Fimprovements.
OL,18,FOn Friday, Harper turns one. It will
OL,19,Fbe a birthday forever tinged with the
OL,20,Fsadness of losing the dad she'll never
OL,21,Fget to meet.
