OL,3,C'No one should have to have
OL,4,Ccongratulations and condolences on the
OL,5,Csame day'
OL,7,F"We remained concerned, however, that
OL,8,Fthe coroner has had to issue a
OL,9,FPrevention of Future Deaths report to
OL,10,Fensure that other families do not have
OL,11,Fto go through what Rebecca has had to
OL,12,Fendure for the last year.
OL,14,F"We hope that the Trust now takes
OL,15,Fsteps to make changes to practices and
OL,16,Fpolicies, to save further lives being
OL,17,Flost, unnecessarily."
